VGI2EIF is a quick tool for converting VGM Maker instruments into FM
instruments for use by Echo.

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Provided in this package:

   * Tool source code
   * VGI format documentation
   * EIF format documentation

The source code for the tool is licensed under the zlib license (see
tool/LICENSE).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is a command line tool. It takes an instrument generated in VGM Maker
(".vgi" extension) and outputs a FM instrument in the format used by the Echo
sound engine (usually ".eif" extension).

You can build this tool by using the makefile or just compiling together all
the C files. This tool is licensed under the zlib license.

To convert a VGI file into EIF:

   vgi2eif «infile» «outfile»

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

It's suggested to use the ".eif" extension for Echo FM instruments (e.g.
"example.eif").

